The Law of Diminishing ReturnsSports science landmark meta-analyses—such as the landmark volume studies by Dr. Brad Schoenfeld—clearly demonstrate a dose-response relationship between weekly sets and muscle growth. The return on your time investment breaks down into three distinct tiers:

Low Volume (1–4 sets/week): Generates roughly 60–65% of your maximum potential muscle growth.
It is highly efficient for the time spent but far from optimal.

Moderate Volume (5–9 sets/week): Captures about 80–85% of your potential gains. This is the "sweet spot" for busy lifters.

High Volume (10–20 sets/week): Unlocks 100% of your genetic hypertrophy potential for that training cycle.


